{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_bc732cb54a0e4008a601a8f3","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Phase 1 Foundation — Task Reference\n2\t\n3\t## Global Rules\n4\t- All files created in this task are NEW files — do not modify any existing files\n5\t- Use TypeScript strict mode, match the existing project style (see `app/utils/auth.ts` for patterns)\n6\t- Import paths use relative paths without extensions (Next.js convention)\n7\t- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts`, `app/utils/crypto.ts`, or any existing files\n8\t- Working directory: `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment`\n9\t\n10\t## Loop\n11\t- Implement: read this file, do Task N. Run `npx tsc --noEmit`. Commit.\n12\t- Review: read this file, check Task N. Fix or say \"all clean.\"\n13\t- Max 3 review rounds per task.\n14\t\n15\t---\n16\t\n17\t## Task 1: GCS Read/Write Utility\n18\t\n19\t- Slug: `gcs-utility`\n20\t- Goal: Create a thin GCS wrapper that reads/writes JSON files and lists files with optional date filtering.\n21\t\n22\t### Read These Files First\n23\t1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth.ts` (lines 1-10) — import style, TypeScript patterns used in this project\n24\t2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/package.json` (lines 69-71) — confirms `@google-cloud/storage@^7` is in optionalDependencies\n25\t3. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/constants.py` (lines 30-62) — GCS bucket paths and file locations to replicate\n26\t\n27\t### Changes Required\n28\t\n29\t**Create `app/utils/gcs.ts`:**\n30\t\n31\t```typescript\n32\t// @google-cloud/storage is an optionalDependency — use dynamic import() so the module\n33\t// loads without crashing when the package isn't installed (e.g., local dev without GCS).\n34\t// Lazy singleton pattern: first call to getStorage() does the import and caches.\n35\t\n36\tlet storageInstance: InstanceType<typeof import('@google-cloud/storage').Storage> | null = null;\n37\t\n38\tasync function getStorage() {\n39\t  if (storageInstance) return storageInstance;\n40\t  try {\n41\t    const { Storage } = await import('@google-cloud/storage');\n42\t    storageInstance = new Storage();\n43\t    return storageInstance;\n44\t  } catch {\n45\t    throw new Error('GCS not available — install @google-cloud/storage');\n46\t  }\n47\t}\n48\t\n49\tfunction getBucketName(): string {\n50\t  const name = process.env.GCS_BUCKET_NAME;\n51\t  if (!name) throw new Error('GCS_BUCKET_NAME env var not set');\n52\t  return name;\n53\t}\n54\t\n55\t// GCS path constants (ported from constants.py lines 30-62)\n56\texport const GCS_PATHS = {\n57\t  USER_CONFIG_PREFIX: 'user_data/',\n58\t  USER_SUMMARY_BY_USER: 'user_data/summary/user_summary_by_user.json',\n59\t  USER_SUMMARY_BY_FORM_TYPE: 'user_data/summary/user_summary_by_form_type.json',\n60\t  USER_INTEGRITY_BY_USER: 'user_data/integrity/user_integrity_by_user.json',\n61\t  APPLICANT_ENROLLED_LIST: 'user_data/integrity/applicant_enrolled_list.csv',\n62\t  ADMIN_CONFIG: 'config/admin_config.json',\n63\t  FORM_CONFIG_PREFIX: 'config/forms/',\n64\t  TTC_COUNTRY_AND_DATES: 'config/forms/ttc_country_and_dates.json',\n65\t  TEMP_PREFIX: 'tmp/',\n66\t} as const;\n67\t\n68\texport interface FileMetadata {\n69\t  name: string;\n70\t  updated: Date;\n71\t  timeCreated: Date;\n72\t}\n73\t\n74\texport async function readJson(path: string): Promise<unknown> { ... }\n75\t// Downloads file, JSON.parse, returns parsed object. Throws on not-found.\n76\t\n77\texport async function writeJson(path: string, data: unknown): Promise<void> { ... }\n78\t// JSON.stringify, upload with content-type text/plain (matching legacy gcs.open 'w' pattern)\n79\t\n80\texport async function readText(path: string): Promise<string> { ... }\n81\t// Downloads file, returns string. For CSV and other non-JSON.\n82\t\n83\texport async function writeText(path: string, content: string): Promise<void> { ... }\n84\t\n85\texport async function listFiles(prefix: string, minUpdated?: Date): Promise<FileMetadata[]> { ... }\n86\t// Lists files under prefix. If minUpdated provided, filter to files updated after that date.\n87\t// Uses file.getMetadata() — read top-level `updated` and `timeCreated` fields (NOT metadata.metadata.*).\n88\t\n89\texport async function fileExists(path: string): Promise<boolean> { ... }\n90\t\n91\texport async function getFileMetadata(path: string): Promise<FileMetadata> { ... }\n92\t// Calls file.getMetadata(), returns { name, updated: new Date(metadata.updated), timeCreated: new Date(metadata.timeCreated) }\n93\t```\n94\t\n95\t- `@google-cloud/storage` is optional — the dynamic `import()` pattern above handles this. All functions that need Storage call `await getStorage()` which will throw if the package isn't installed.\n96\t- `writeJson` should use `JSON.stringify(data)` with no indentation (matching legacy compact JSON)\n97\t- Retry params: do NOT add retry logic — keep it simple, let callers retry\n98\t\n99\t### Constraints\n100\t- Do NOT add caching — callers decide if/when to cache\n101\t- Do NOT add logging — callers decide if/when to log\n102\t- Do NOT create any test files\n103\t\n104\t### Verification\n105\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n106\t- Commit message: `feat: add GCS read/write utility`\n107\t\n108\t---\n109\t\n110\t## Task 2: Login Endpoint\n111\t\n112\t- Slug: `login-endpoint`\n113\t- Goal: Create a `/api/auth/login` POST endpoint that issues session tokens in dev mode and verifies Google ID tokens in production.\n114\t\n115\t### Read These Files First\n116\t1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth.ts` — full file. Contains `generateSessionToken()`, `getAuthMode()`, `getSessionMaxAge()`, `verifySessionToken()`. You will IMPORT from this file, not modify it.\n117\t2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/crypto.ts` (lines 1-20) — contains `getSessionHmacSecret()` which you need for generating tokens\n118\t\n119\t### Changes Required\n120\t\n121\t**Create `app/api/auth/login/route.ts`:**\n122\t\n123\t```typescript\n124\timport { generateSessionToken } from '../../../utils/auth';\n125\timport { getSessionHmacSecret } from '../../../utils/crypto';\n126\t\n127\texport async function POST(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n128\t  const mode = process.env.AUTH_MODE === 'platform' ? 'platform' : 'session';\n129\t  const isDev = process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development';\n130\t\n131\t  // Platform mode: login not needed (IAP handles auth)\n132\t  if (mode === 'platform') {\n133\t    return Response.json({ error: 'Login not available in platform mode' }, { status: 404 });\n134\t  }\n135\t\n136\t  // Session mode\n137\t  const body = await request.json() as Record<string, unknown>;\n138\t\n139\t  if (isDev) {\n140\t    // Dev mode: accept email-only, no verification\n141\t    const email = typeof body.email === 'string' ? body.email.trim() : '';\n142\t    if (!email || !email.includes('@')) {\n143\t      return Response.json({ error: 'Valid email required' }, { status: 400 });\n144\t    }\n145\t    const secret = getSessionHmacSecret();\n146\t    const token = generateSessionToken(email, secret);\n147\t    return Response.json({ token, email });\n148\t  }\n149\t\n150\t  // Production session mode: verify Google ID token\n151\t  const idToken = typeof body.id_token === 'string' ? body.id_token : '';\n152\t  if (!idToken) {\n153\t    return Response.json({ error: 'id_token required' }, { status: 400 });\n154\t  }\n155\t\n156\t  const clientId = process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID;\n157\t  if (!clientId) {\n158\t    return Response.json({ error: 'Server misconfigured: GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID not set' }, { status: 500 });\n159\t  }\n160\t\n161\t  // Verify Google ID token using jose\n162\t  // Fetch Google JWKS, verify audience=GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, issuer=https://accounts.google.com, algorithm=RS256\n163\t  // Use jose's createRemoteJWKSet for JWKS fetching with built-in caching\n164\t  try {\n165\t    const { createRemoteJWKSet, jwtVerify } = await import('jose');\n166\t    const JWKS = createRemoteJWKSet(new URL('https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v3/certs'));\n167\t    const { payload } = await jwtVerify(idToken, JWKS, {\n168\t      audience: clientId,\n169\t      issuer: 'https://accounts.google.com',\n170\t    });\n171\t    const email = typeof payload.email === 'string' ? payload.email : null;\n172\t    if (!email) {\n173\t      return Response.json({ error: 'No email in token' }, { status: 401 });\n174\t    }\n175\t    const secret = getSessionHmacSecret();\n176\t    const token = generateSessionToken(email, secret);\n177\t    return Response.json({ token, email });\n178\t  } catch {\n179\t    return Response.json({ error: 'Invalid or expired token' }, { status: 401 });\n180\t  }\n181\t}\n182\t```\n183\t\n184\t### Constraints\n185\t- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts` — import only\n186\t- Do NOT add GET handler — login is POST-only\n187\t- `jose` is already a dependency (`package.json` line 59)\n188\t\n189\t### Verification\n190\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n191\t- Commit message: `feat: add login endpoint with dev and production modes`\n192\t\n193\t---\n194\t\n195\t## Task 3: Auth Middleware Helpers\n196\t\n197\t- Slug: `auth-middleware`\n198\t- Goal: Create reusable auth middleware functions for route handlers — requireAuth, requireAdmin, requireAdminForPage, requireAdminOrCron, and variants.\n199\t\n200\t### Read These Files First\n201\t1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth.ts` — full file. Contains `getAuthenticatedUser()` — the unified auth entry point. You will IMPORT this function.\n202\t2. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/constants.py` (lines 84-150) — `LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS` dict. Port this data structure to TS.\n203\t3. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/admin.py` (lines 140-155) — `check_permissions()` method. Port this logic.\n204\t\n205\t### Changes Required\n206\t\n207\t**Create `app/utils/auth-middleware.ts`:**\n208\t\n209\t```typescript\n210\timport { getAuthenticatedUser } from './auth';\n211\t\n212\t// Port of constants.LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS from constants.py:84+\n213\t// NOTE: this is hardcoded for parity — will move to GCS config later\n214\tconst LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS: Record<string, { countries: string[]; report_permissions: string[] }> = {\n215\t  'amit.nair@artofliving.org': {\n216\t    countries: ['US', 'CA'],\n217\t    report_permissions: ['ttc_applicants_summary.html', 'post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html', 'admin_settings.html', 'ttc_applicants_integrity.html'],\n218\t  },\n219\t  // ... (port ALL entries from constants.py lines 84-150+)\n220\t  // Read the file to get the complete list\n221\t};\n222\t\n223\t// Flat list of all admin emails (keys of the permissions dict)\n224\tconst LIST_OF_ADMINS = new Set(Object.keys(LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS));\n225\t\n226\t// Map from Next.js route segments to legacy page keys\n227\tconst ROUTE_TO_PAGE_KEY: Record<string, string> = {\n228\t  'ttc_applicants_summary': 'ttc_applicants_summary.html',\n229\t  'ttc_applicants_reports': 'ttc_applicants_reports.html',\n230\t  'ttc_applicants_integrity': 'ttc_applicants_integrity.html',\n231\t  'settings': 'admin_settings.html',\n232\t  'reports_list': 'ttc_applicants_reports.html',\n233\t  'post_ttc_course_feedback': 'post_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html',\n234\t  'post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback': 'post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html',\n235\t};\n236\t\n237\ttype AuthResult = { email: string } | Response;\n238\t\n239\t// Checks authenticated user\n240\texport async function requireAuth(request: Request): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n241\t\n242\t// Checks user is in LIST_OF_ADMINS (no page-specific permission)\n243\texport async function requireAdmin(request: Request): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n244\t\n245\t// Checks user has permission for a specific page\n246\texport async function requireAdminForPage(request: Request, page: string): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n247\t\n248\t// Checks user has permission for ANY of the listed pages\n249\texport async function requireAdminAnyOf(request: Request, pages: string[]): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n250\t\n251\t// Checks admin list OR cron header\n252\t// Cron trust model: if CRON_SECRET env is set, require x-cron-secret header match.\n253\t// If CRON_SECRET not set, accept x-appengine-cron header (dev mode only).\n254\texport async function requireAdminOrCron(request: Request): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n255\t\n256\t// Checks admin with any-of page permission OR cron header\n257\texport async function requireAdminAnyOfOrCron(request: Request, pages: string[]): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n258\t\n259\t// Helper: check if request has valid cron header\n260\tfunction isCronRequest(request: Request): boolean { ... }\n261\t\n262\t// Helper: check page permission (port of admin.py:140-155 check_permissions)\n263\tfunction checkPermissions(email: string, page: string): boolean {\n264\t  const perms = LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS[email];\n265\t  if (!perms) return false;\n266\t  return perms.report_permissions.includes(page);\n267\t}\n268\t\n269\t// Exports for other modules\n270\texport { LIST_OF_ADMINS, LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS, ROUTE_TO_PAGE_KEY };\n271\t```\n272\t\n273\tAll `require*` functions return `{ email }` on success or a `Response` (401/403 JSON) on failure.\n274\t\n275\t### Constraints\n276\t- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts`\n277\t- Port ALL entries from `constants.py` `LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS` — read the full file to get every email/permission pair\n278\t- The `isCronRequest` helper must implement the CRON_SECRET trust model: when `CRON_SECRET` env var is set, require `x-cron-secret` header to match. When not set, accept `x-appengine-cron: true` header (dev-only fallback).\n279\t\n280\t### Verification\n281\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n282\t- Commit message: `feat: add auth middleware with admin permissions and cron bypass`\n283\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ccb479f-aaae-4fab-ac1e-d4455c698fb3","uuid":"e4cd1684-10ce-431f-8e80-257881623bfd","timestamp":"2026-04-06T09:50:51.316Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/.agent/tasks/task-1-foundation.md","content":"# Phase 1 Foundation — Task Reference\n\n## Global Rules\n- All files created in this task are NEW files — do not modify any existing files\n- Use TypeScript strict mode, match the existing project style (see `app/utils/auth.ts` for patterns)\n- Import paths use relative paths without extensions (Next.js convention)\n- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts`, `app/utils/crypto.ts`, or any existing files\n- Working directory: `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment`\n\n## Loop\n- Implement: read this file, do Task N. Run `npx tsc --noEmit`. Commit.\n- Review: read this file, check Task N. Fix or say \"all clean.\"\n- Max 3 review rounds per task.\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: GCS Read/Write Utility\n\n- Slug: `gcs-utility`\n- Goal: Create a thin GCS wrapper that reads/writes JSON files and lists files with optional date filtering.\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth.ts` (lines 1-10) — import style, TypeScript patterns used in this project\n2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/package.json` (lines 69-71) — confirms `@google-cloud/storage@^7` is in optionalDependencies\n3. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/constants.py` (lines 30-62) — GCS bucket paths and file locations to replicate\n\n### Changes Required\n\n**Create `app/utils/gcs.ts`:**\n\n```typescript\n// @google-cloud/storage is an optionalDependency — use dynamic import() so the module\n// loads without crashing when the package isn't installed (e.g., local dev without GCS).\n// Lazy singleton pattern: first call to getStorage() does the import and caches.\n\nlet storageInstance: InstanceType<typeof import('@google-cloud/storage').Storage> | null = null;\n\nasync function getStorage() {\n  if (storageInstance) return storageInstance;\n  try {\n    const { Storage } = await import('@google-cloud/storage');\n    storageInstance = new Storage();\n    return storageInstance;\n  } catch {\n    throw new Error('GCS not available — install @google-cloud/storage');\n  }\n}\n\nfunction getBucketName(): string {\n  const name = process.env.GCS_BUCKET_NAME;\n  if (!name) throw new Error('GCS_BUCKET_NAME env var not set');\n  return name;\n}\n\n// GCS path constants (ported from constants.py lines 30-62)\nexport const GCS_PATHS = {\n  USER_CONFIG_PREFIX: 'user_data/',\n  USER_SUMMARY_BY_USER: 'user_data/summary/user_summary_by_user.json',\n  USER_SUMMARY_BY_FORM_TYPE: 'user_data/summary/user_summary_by_form_type.json',\n  USER_INTEGRITY_BY_USER: 'user_data/integrity/user_integrity_by_user.json',\n  APPLICANT_ENROLLED_LIST: 'user_data/integrity/applicant_enrolled_list.csv',\n  ADMIN_CONFIG: 'config/admin_config.json',\n  FORM_CONFIG_PREFIX: 'config/forms/',\n  TTC_COUNTRY_AND_DATES: 'config/forms/ttc_country_and_dates.json',\n  TEMP_PREFIX: 'tmp/',\n} as const;\n\nexport interface FileMetadata {\n  name: string;\n  updated: Date;\n  timeCreated: Date;\n}\n\nexport async function readJson(path: string): Promise<unknown> { ... }\n// Downloads file, JSON.parse, returns parsed object. Throws on not-found.\n\nexport async function writeJson(path: string, data: unknown): Promise<void> { ... }\n// JSON.stringify, upload with content-type text/plain (matching legacy gcs.open 'w' pattern)\n\nexport async function readText(path: string): Promise<string> { ... }\n// Downloads file, returns string. For CSV and other non-JSON.\n\nexport async function writeText(path: string, content: string): Promise<void> { ... }\n\nexport async function listFiles(prefix: string, minUpdated?: Date): Promise<FileMetadata[]> { ... }\n// Lists files under prefix. If minUpdated provided, filter to files updated after that date.\n// Uses file.getMetadata() — read top-level `updated` and `timeCreated` fields (NOT metadata.metadata.*).\n\nexport async function fileExists(path: string): Promise<boolean> { ... }\n\nexport async function getFileMetadata(path: string): Promise<FileMetadata> { ... }\n// Calls file.getMetadata(), returns { name, updated: new Date(metadata.updated), timeCreated: new Date(metadata.timeCreated) }\n```\n\n- `@google-cloud/storage` is optional — the dynamic `import()` pattern above handles this. All functions that need Storage call `await getStorage()` which will throw if the package isn't installed.\n- `writeJson` should use `JSON.stringify(data)` with no indentation (matching legacy compact JSON)\n- Retry params: do NOT add retry logic — keep it simple, let callers retry\n\n### Constraints\n- Do NOT add caching — callers decide if/when to cache\n- Do NOT add logging — callers decide if/when to log\n- Do NOT create any test files\n\n### Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n- Commit message: `feat: add GCS read/write utility`\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Login Endpoint\n\n- Slug: `login-endpoint`\n- Goal: Create a `/api/auth/login` POST endpoint that issues session tokens in dev mode and verifies Google ID tokens in production.\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth.ts` — full file. Contains `generateSessionToken()`, `getAuthMode()`, `getSessionMaxAge()`, `verifySessionToken()`. You will IMPORT from this file, not modify it.\n2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/crypto.ts` (lines 1-20) — contains `getSessionHmacSecret()` which you need for generating tokens\n\n### Changes Required\n\n**Create `app/api/auth/login/route.ts`:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { generateSessionToken } from '../../../utils/auth';\nimport { getSessionHmacSecret } from '../../../utils/crypto';\n\nexport async function POST(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n  const mode = process.env.AUTH_MODE === 'platform' ? 'platform' : 'session';\n  const isDev = process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development';\n\n  // Platform mode: login not needed (IAP handles auth)\n  if (mode === 'platform') {\n    return Response.json({ error: 'Login not available in platform mode' }, { status: 404 });\n  }\n\n  // Session mode\n  const body = await request.json() as Record<string, unknown>;\n\n  if (isDev) {\n    // Dev mode: accept email-only, no verification\n    const email = typeof body.email === 'string' ? body.email.trim() : '';\n    if (!email || !email.includes('@')) {\n      return Response.json({ error: 'Valid email required' }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n    const secret = getSessionHmacSecret();\n    const token = generateSessionToken(email, secret);\n    return Response.json({ token, email });\n  }\n\n  // Production session mode: verify Google ID token\n  const idToken = typeof body.id_token === 'string' ? body.id_token : '';\n  if (!idToken) {\n    return Response.json({ error: 'id_token required' }, { status: 400 });\n  }\n\n  const clientId = process.env.GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID;\n  if (!clientId) {\n    return Response.json({ error: 'Server misconfigured: GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID not set' }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n\n  // Verify Google ID token using jose\n  // Fetch Google JWKS, verify audience=GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, issuer=https://accounts.google.com, algorithm=RS256\n  // Use jose's createRemoteJWKSet for JWKS fetching with built-in caching\n  try {\n    const { createRemoteJWKSet, jwtVerify } = await import('jose');\n    const JWKS = createRemoteJWKSet(new URL('https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v3/certs'));\n    const { payload } = await jwtVerify(idToken, JWKS, {\n      audience: clientId,\n      issuer: 'https://accounts.google.com',\n    });\n    const email = typeof payload.email === 'string' ? payload.email : null;\n    if (!email) {\n      return Response.json({ error: 'No email in token' }, { status: 401 });\n    }\n    const secret = getSessionHmacSecret();\n    const token = generateSessionToken(email, secret);\n    return Response.json({ token, email });\n  } catch {\n    return Response.json({ error: 'Invalid or expired token' }, { status: 401 });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Constraints\n- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts` — import only\n- Do NOT add GET handler — login is POST-only\n- `jose` is already a dependency (`package.json` line 59)\n\n### Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n- Commit message: `feat: add login endpoint with dev and production modes`\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Auth Middleware Helpers\n\n- Slug: `auth-middleware`\n- Goal: Create reusable auth middleware functions for route handlers — requireAuth, requireAdmin, requireAdminForPage, requireAdminOrCron, and variants.\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth.ts` — full file. Contains `getAuthenticatedUser()` — the unified auth entry point. You will IMPORT this function.\n2. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/constants.py` (lines 84-150) — `LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS` dict. Port this data structure to TS.\n3. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/admin.py` (lines 140-155) — `check_permissions()` method. Port this logic.\n\n### Changes Required\n\n**Create `app/utils/auth-middleware.ts`:**\n\n```typescript\nimport { getAuthenticatedUser } from './auth';\n\n// Port of constants.LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS from constants.py:84+\n// NOTE: this is hardcoded for parity — will move to GCS config later\nconst LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS: Record<string, { countries: string[]; report_permissions: string[] }> = {\n  'amit.nair@artofliving.org': {\n    countries: ['US', 'CA'],\n    report_permissions: ['ttc_applicants_summary.html', 'post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html', 'admin_settings.html', 'ttc_applicants_integrity.html'],\n  },\n  // ... (port ALL entries from constants.py lines 84-150+)\n  // Read the file to get the complete list\n};\n\n// Flat list of all admin emails (keys of the permissions dict)\nconst LIST_OF_ADMINS = new Set(Object.keys(LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS));\n\n// Map from Next.js route segments to legacy page keys\nconst ROUTE_TO_PAGE_KEY: Record<string, string> = {\n  'ttc_applicants_summary': 'ttc_applicants_summary.html',\n  'ttc_applicants_reports': 'ttc_applicants_reports.html',\n  'ttc_applicants_integrity': 'ttc_applicants_integrity.html',\n  'settings': 'admin_settings.html',\n  'reports_list': 'ttc_applicants_reports.html',\n  'post_ttc_course_feedback': 'post_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html',\n  'post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback': 'post_sahaj_ttc_course_feedback_summary.html',\n};\n\ntype AuthResult = { email: string } | Response;\n\n// Checks authenticated user\nexport async function requireAuth(request: Request): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n\n// Checks user is in LIST_OF_ADMINS (no page-specific permission)\nexport async function requireAdmin(request: Request): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n\n// Checks user has permission for a specific page\nexport async function requireAdminForPage(request: Request, page: string): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n\n// Checks user has permission for ANY of the listed pages\nexport async function requireAdminAnyOf(request: Request, pages: string[]): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n\n// Checks admin list OR cron header\n// Cron trust model: if CRON_SECRET env is set, require x-cron-secret header match.\n// If CRON_SECRET not set, accept x-appengine-cron header (dev mode only).\nexport async function requireAdminOrCron(request: Request): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n\n// Checks admin with any-of page permission OR cron header\nexport async function requireAdminAnyOfOrCron(request: Request, pages: string[]): Promise<AuthResult> { ... }\n\n// Helper: check if request has valid cron header\nfunction isCronRequest(request: Request): boolean { ... }\n\n// Helper: check page permission (port of admin.py:140-155 check_permissions)\nfunction checkPermissions(email: string, page: string): boolean {\n  const perms = LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS[email];\n  if (!perms) return false;\n  return perms.report_permissions.includes(page);\n}\n\n// Exports for other modules\nexport { LIST_OF_ADMINS, LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS, ROUTE_TO_PAGE_KEY };\n```\n\nAll `require*` functions return `{ email }` on success or a `Response` (401/403 JSON) on failure.\n\n### Constraints\n- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts`\n- Port ALL entries from `constants.py` `LIST_OF_ADMIN_PERMISSIONS` — read the full file to get every email/permission pair\n- The `isCronRequest` helper must implement the CRON_SECRET trust model: when `CRON_SECRET` env var is set, require `x-cron-secret` header to match. When not set, accept `x-appengine-cron: true` header (dev-only fallback).\n\n### Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n- Commit message: `feat: add auth middleware with admin permissions and cron bypass`\n","numLines":283,"startLine":1,"totalLines":283}}}
